<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
This is the largest longhorn beetle encountered in the Macau SAR during the current census, attaining a total length of 24-36 mm and a maximum width of 8-11 mm. Adults are active from late spring till mid-autumn, both during the day and night. The larvae burrow in a wide variety of forest trees, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lam" authorityYear="1789" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Moraceae" genus="Artocarpus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Artocarpus heterophyllus" order="Urticales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="heterophyllus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Artocarpus heterophyllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lecythidaceae" genus="Careya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Careya arborea" order="Polemoniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Careya arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Gastropoda" family="Ficidae" genus="Ficus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ficus" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ficus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Mangifera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Mangifera" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Mangifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., from India through southeast Asia and south China, including Hong Kong (
<bibRefCitation author="Easton, ER" journalOrPublisher="Entomological News" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="105 - 111" refId="B36" refString="Easton, ER, 1991. Annotated list of insects of Macau observed during 1989. Entomological News 102 (2): 105 - 111" title="Annotated list of insects of Macau observed during 1989." volume="102" year="1991">Easton 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11609/JoTT.o4007.7879-901" author="Kumawat, MM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Threatened Taxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="7879 - 7901" refId="B75" refString="Kumawat, MM, Mamocha Singh, K, Ramamurthy, VV, 2015. A checklist of the Long-horned Beetles (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Arunachal Pradesh, northeastern India with several new reports. Journal of Threatened Taxa 7 (12): 7879 - 7901, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11609/JoTT.o4007.7879-901" title="A checklist of the Long-horned Beetles (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) of Arunachal Pradesh, northeastern India with several new reports." url="https://doi.org/10.11609/JoTT.o4007.7879-901" volume="7" year="2015">Kumawat et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
